(2938, 1, '2014-10-15 04:16:33', '2014-10-15 04:16:33', '<div class="one withsmallpadding " ><div class="page_content_wrapper"><div style="text-align:center">\n<h1 style="font-size:26px;font-style:italic;font-weight:600;">NAMASTE &#038; Welcome to Nepalaya Explorer</h1>\n</p>\n<p>Nepalaya Explorer Born after my Two decades of working experience in Nepal and abroad as a river guide and Adventure Leader. I started very young age, without hiding, I started from Zero point as a Dish washer, cleaning campsite after trip and before, supporting role for senior helper for transporting clients luggage’s by local truck to the campsite and carrying down the campsite middle of the sunny day and setup the campsite where the Sweat drain from  head to Toe, end of the day on my sandy bed “most of the night without sleeping bag &#038; matt” videolaizing river safety instruction and conversation between raft guide and clients for my improvement to become a raft guide in future, and approaching clients to speak English and learn from them finely my senior raft guide spot me ride away and take me down the river by raft and put me as a river helper and train me for a next generation raft guide, (I still remember that day as my Success till now and forever, and him as a GURU)  As a rafting guide in the country running numbers of rivers expedition with  great companies,  been Iran as a instructor for helping Iranian rafting industries to run the trip commercially ,  working as a senior raft guide in Iceland and since 2007 as a adventure manager in northern Myanmar  in one of the world known Malikha Lodge Luxury hotel and train the youth as my GURU taught me twenty years ago to reach this level and opportunities to become a company owner after many, many years of Hard working to setup my new Revolution company to provide quality standard service, friendly and family hospitality and environment and highly unforgettable safety priority. Nepalaya Explorer is not only business for me, it is  just a way to get out myself and have the best social adventure I can do support the community and preserve the God gift Mother nature. What I learn from my two decades of experience is wherever Nepalaya Explorer going to have trip on this BLIND MOTHER NATURE me and my team promises that we not gone a HURT because many companies did that already by leaving their Trash behind, SHE can’t sought at you but our team can hear her from our heart because we know our country by HEART, also we educate the local people to make their habit to not to throw the trash on the way. Very few companies have been involved in community work and preserving the environment in reality on the field.<br />\nThese days it easy to put up a great web page and have everything looking impressive on the web but we pride ourselves in providing trips and surprise treat on what you see is what you get basis!</p>\n<div style="font-weight:bold;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1px;color:#b63327;margin-top:15px;">Travel . Tours . Adventure</div>\n</div>\n<p>\n</div></div>\n<div class="one withpadding ppb_team " style="background:#f3f3f3;" ><div class="page_content_wrapper" style="text-align:center"><h2 class="ppb_title">Our Team</h2><br/><br/><div class="team_wrapper"><div class="one_fourth animated1 "><div class="post_img static team animate " style="margin-bottom:10px"><img class="team_pic" src="http://nepalayaexplorer.com/wp-includes/images/media/default.png" alt=""/></div><br class="clear"/><div id="portfolio_desc_2620" class="portfolio_desc team shortcode "><h5>Mark Anthony</h5><span class="portfolio_excerpt">Co-Founder & CEO</span><p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit. Aenean commodo ligula eget dolor sociis natoque </p><ul class="social_wrapper team"><li><a title="Mark Anthony on Twitter" target="_blank" class="tooltip" href="http://twitter.com/#"><i class="fa fa-twitter"></i></a></li><li><a title="Mark Anthony on Facebook" target="_blank" class="tooltip" href="http://